Package: lidR
Type: Package
Title: Airborne LiDAR Data Manipulations and Visualisation for Forestry
    Applications
Version: 0.6.0
Date: 2016-04-09
Author: Jean-Romain Roussel
Maintainer: Jean-Romain Roussel <jean-romain.roussel.1@ulaval.ca>
Description: This package provide airborne LiDAR interface for data
    visualisation and manipulation. It has been designed mainly for forestry
    application. lidR package allows computation of digital elevation model
    of canopy, point classification based on geographic shapefiles, space
    rasterization, computation of derived metric, point filtering, artificial point
    reduction and others manipulations.
License: GPL-2
Depends:
    R (>= 3.2.0),methods,data.table,dplyr,dtplyr,magrittr
Imports:
    rgl,grDevices,reshape2,geometry,tools,parallel,RcppArmadillo,fields,bitops,raster,sp,rgdal,plyr,rgeos
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 5.0.1
